# Downloads and local vs remote playback

Apply when editing download stores, playback URL resolution, or offline behavior.

## URL resolution

In `songToTrack(song)` (useAudioStore):

- `localUri = song.localUri || useMusicDownloadsStore.getState().getLocalUri(song.id)`.
- Then `url = localUri || (song.uri if non-empty)`.
- Local always wins when available; Plex bitrate is applied only when not local and not podcast.

## Podcasts

- Episodes get `localUri` or stream URL at call sites (`toPlayableSong` in types/podcast, feed/episode screens, PodcastEpisodeItem).
- Resume: downloaded episodes use `usePodcastDownloadsStore.getState().getResumeAt(song.id)`; streamed use progress store.
- Progress is saved to both progress store and (when downloaded) `updateResumeAt`.

## Offline

- `useOfflineModeStore` and `useOfflineFilteredLibrary` restrict library UI to downloaded content.
- Playback code does not check offline mode; it only uses the URL from `songToTrack`.
- When offline mode is on, only local URLs are surfaced via the filtered library.
